        "timestamp": "2019-07-18 09:18:51.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThanks, I wasn't aware of this @Rule.\n\nI think it will not work for us for two reasons:\n1) We will need to switch this class to JUnit instead of TestNG. (Although not a hard change.)\n2) Issue I'm trying to resolve here resides in EPSDK'd function `org.onap.portalsdk.core.util.SystemProperties#getProperty`, where system properties are read through a static `Environment` instance which is already populated with system.properties values. A @Rule will need to affect this instance, not the _standard_ `System.getProperty()`.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
